The High Court is hearing arguments in the DA&#8217;s application to have Hlaudi Motsoeneng removed as an SABC employee. CAPE TOWN The lawyer for Hlaudi Motsoeneng, the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) group executive of corporate affairs, said no court can order that he be fired based on the instruction of a political party. #Hlaudi du Toit adds the DA is trying to dictate to the #SABC who to hire. KBThe Western Cape High Court heard arguments in the Democratic Alliance s (DA) application to have Motsoeneng removed as an SABC employee on Thursday.Motsoeneng smiled and nodded as his legal representative, advocate Stephan du Toit, highlighted why the DA's application was premature. #Hlaudi his lawyer adds the the role of a disciplinary process is not always to arrive at a dismissal. KBDu Toit said Motsoeneng's rights should be upheld and emphasised that the DA cannot dictate to the SABC on who they should hire.He conceded that Motsoeneng had apologised for wrongly completing his job application form. The DA's legal team argued that the SABC had failed to comply with remedial action in the Public Protector's report. Earlier this month, Parliament established an ad hoc committee to conduct inquiry into the fitness of the SABC board.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)